  <item nodeId="node-197">
    <command xml:space="preserve">open door</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">That's already open.&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-198"/>
    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-198">
    <command xml:space="preserve">close door</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">Try as you might, a mystical force prevents you from closing the important door.&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-199"/>
    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-199">
    <command xml:space="preserve">close rucksack</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">Try as you might, a mystical force prevents you from closing the leather rucksack.&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-210">
    <command xml:space="preserve">test summon</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">(Testing.)&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;[1] d&#x000A;If you get any closer to the aerie without summoning mist first, the guards would surely see you.  It's why, as a Bostrat, you were originally chosen to go on this mission.&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;[2] n&#x000A;You'll need to SUMMON MIST first, to cloak your descent.&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;[3] summon mist&#x000A;Calling on your heritage as a Bostrat, you summon moisture from the air, and it slowly coalesces into a creeping grey mist, obscuring you from sight.  In gentler times, you would be doing this to ensure the growth of the fields and forests; now you must use it to hide from prying eyes that would keep you from your quarry.&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;[4] d&#x000A;&#x000A;Great Hall Landing Cradle&#x000A;The Landing Cradle of the Great Hall spreads out over nearly a quarter of the vast building.  During your time here, you learned this was so that when a number of important guests and their retinues arrive at the same time, they can land simultaneously, instead of one after the other, which some would invariably take as meaning "in order of importance".&#x000A;&#x000A;To the north is the Royal Quarters, the Librum to the east, {other places LS DEBUG}, and as always, you can return to the skies.&#x000A;&#x000A;You can see an important door here.&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;[5] u&#x000A;&#x000A;High Above the Royal Aerie&#x000A;Your summoned mist both obscures you and blocks you from seeing the Royal Aerie.  But you've already memorized its layout, and how it relates to today's air currents, winds, and thermals.  Royal quarters to the north, well defended by circling Raven clan guards.  The librum to the east.  {LS DEBUG: a few other rooms.  Presumably.  Kitchen, Barracks, Chapel(?), }  In the center of the Aerie (and directly below you) is the Great Hall.&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-130">
    <command xml:space="preserve">x me</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">As good-looking as ever.  Up yours, Katsaris!&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-131"/>
    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-131">
    <command xml:space="preserve">#woot</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">I didn't understand that sentence.&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-132"/>
    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-132">
    <command xml:space="preserve"># woot</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">Noted.&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-133">
    <command xml:space="preserve">x me.</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">As good-looking as ever.  Up yours, Katsaris!&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-143">
    <command xml:space="preserve">x mist</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">The cloud layer today is too high for a naturally obscuring mist; you'll have to summon it yourself.&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-144"/>
    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-144">
    <command xml:space="preserve">summon mist</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">Calling on your heritage as a Bostrat, you summon moisture from the air, and it slowly coalesces into a creeping grey mist, obscuring you from sight.  In gentler times, you would be doing this to ensure the growth of the fields and forests; now you must use it to hide from prying eyes that would keep you from your quarry.&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-145"/>
    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-145">
    <command xml:space="preserve">summon mist</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">You draw even more moisture from the air, feeding it into the mist.  It's still just as obscuring as before, but you feel safer, as you always do in the midst of clouds.&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-146"/>
    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-146">
    <command xml:space="preserve">x mist</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">Grey mist swirls and surrounds you, covering you like a blanket.&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-147"/>
    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-147">
    <command xml:space="preserve">i</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">You are carrying:&#x000A;  a brown rucksack (being worn, and open)&#x000A;    a purple capsa of rezrov (closed)&#x000A;    a gold capsa of FOO (closed)&#x000A;    a red capsa of BAR (closed)&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-148"/>
    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-148">
    <command xml:space="preserve">l</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">High Above the Royal Aerie&#x000A;Your summoned mist both obscures you and blocks you from seeing the Royal Aerie.  But you've already memorized its layout, and how it relates to today's air currents, winds, and thermals.  Royal quarters to the north.  Well defended by circling Raven clan guards.  The librum to the east.  &#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-149"/>
    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-149">
    <command xml:space="preserve">x aerie</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">The Royal Aerie was grown and shaped by generations of Throckials, and now towers over the surrounding forest canopy.  Lush shades of browns and reds, often woven together in intricate patterns or pictures cover every landing cradle and wall.&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-150"/>
    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-150">
    <command xml:space="preserve">x purple</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">The purple capsa turned out to contain a scroll of rezrov, as became evident when every buckle and lock in your village flew open when you opened the capsa to investigate.  It is closed, preventing the power of the scroll from affecting the area.&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-151"/>
    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-151">
    <command xml:space="preserve">open purple</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">You open the purple capsa of rezrov, revealing a scroll of rezrov.&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-152"/>
    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-152">
    <command xml:space="preserve">x purple</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">The purple capsa turned out to contain a scroll of rezrov.  It is open, allowing the scroll's power to open and hold open any closed object in the area.&#x000A;&#x000A;In the purple capsa of rezrov is a scroll of rezrov.&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-153"/>
    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-153">
    <command xml:space="preserve">x scroll</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">While "REZROV" can be clearly read at the top of the scroll, the rest is in some arcane script you (and the people and sages of your village) were unfamiliar with.&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-154"/>
    </children>
  </item>
  <item nodeId="node-154">
    <command xml:space="preserve">x rezrov</command>
    <result xml:space="preserve">(the scroll of rezrov)&#x000A;While "REZROV" can be clearly read at the top of the scroll, the rest is in some arcane script you are unfamiliar with.&#x000A;&#x000A;&gt;</result>
    <commentary xml:space="preserve"></commentary>
    <changed>NO</changed>
    <children>
      <child nodeId="node-155"/>
    </children>
  </item>
